{{lowercase|ubuntu-restricted-extras}} {{Infobox software | name = ubuntu-restricted-extras | logo = | screenshot = | caption = | collapsible = | author = | developer = various | released = | latest release version = 42<ref name="REMaverick">[http://packages.ubuntu.com/maverick/ubuntu-restricted-extras Package: ubuntu-restricted-extras in Maverick Meerkat]</ref> | latest release date = | latest preview version = 43<ref name="RENatty">[http://packages.ubuntu.com/natty/ubuntu-restricted-extras Package: ubuntu-restricted-extras in Natty Narwhal]</ref> | latest preview date = | frequently updated = | programming language = | operating system = | platform = [[Ubuntu (operating system)|Ubuntu]] ([[Linux]]) | size = | language = English | status = Current | genre = | license = Various (Ubuntu MOTU Developers) | website = [https://help.ubuntu.com/community/RestrictedFormats Ubuntu wiki RestrictedFormats] }} '''ubuntu-restricted-extras''' is a [[software package (installation)|software package]] for the computer [[operating system]] [[Ubuntu (operating system)|Ubuntu]] that allows the user to install essential software which is not already included due to legal or copyright reasons.
It is a meta-package that installs: *Support for [[MP3]] and unencrypted [[DVD-Video|DVD]] playback *Microsoft [[TrueType]] core fonts *[[Adobe Flash Player|Flash plugin]] *[[codec]]s for common audio and video files
The [[Medibuntu]] project has similar aims to the ubuntu-restricted-extras package.
== Contents == The ubuntu-restricted-extras is a metapackage and has the following dependencies<ref name="REMaverick" />: * flashplugin-installer * gstreamer0.10-ffmpeg * gstreamer0.10-fluendo-mp3 * gstreamer0.10-pitfdll * gstreamer0.10-plugins-bad * gstreamer0.10-plugins-ugly * gstreamer0.10-plugins-bad-multiverse * gstreamer0.10-plugins-ugly-multiverse * icedtea6-plugin * libavcodec-extra-52 * libmp4v2-0 * ttf-mscorefonts-installer * unrar As of Ubuntu 10.10, several of these dependencies are included indirectly, through another metapackage called ubuntu-restricted-addons.
==Inclusion== Due to the legal status of the software included in ubuntu-restricted-extras, the package is not included by default on any Ubuntu CDs. However, some distributions, such as [[Super OS]], do bundle the package on their installation CDs.{{Citation needed|date=September 2010}}
